post_text: As the sunsets across the lake, we bid farewell to the Class of 2020. Although, graduation might not have been what you imagined your graduation would be, it was a beautiful celebration. You have graduated and are on your way to an amazing new chapter in your life, and will be in our memories and our hearts. Best of luck to all in the next chapter of your life. CONGRATULATIONS!

Dear Seniors and Parents,
At this time and moving through June, the 10 person limit on gatherings is still being mandated by the governor. Please hold the graduation date of June 7 at 1:00 pm on your calendars. We are doing our best to plan something that enables our seniors to graduate while still honoring social distancing and CDC recommendations. We will send out more details as the plan comes to full fruition. Stay healthy and safe! Heather King, Head of School

PLEASE FIND THEM ON INSTAGRAM!

post_text:
On Friday March 20th from 5:30 pm to 8:00 pm, Monkitree Art Gallery in Gardiner is celebrating Maine's Bicentennial through the lens of students from Maine Arts Academy.
By capturing Maine's unique history in the form of architecture designed and constructed almost two centuries before they were born, the students of Maine Arts Academy explored composition and light while using digital technology to showcase the beautiful, historic buildings among us.

post_text:
This is the first year our school has a Dance Competition Team. Under the Direction of Holly Gannett, these students will be attending their very first competition on March 1st at the Waterville Opera House. They will perform a Hip-Hop routine that they have been working on this semester and have spent countless hours with the help of their parents with fundraising efforts to make this happen.
We are pleased to provide this new opportunity for our students.

Thanks M&I Dancewear for these great uniforms.

Hello all! My 2 daughters will be losing their ride to the bus stop in the mornings in February, and I'm wondering if there's anyone out there that can help. Their ride would be from Kennebec savings bank on Main Street in Winthrop to the Cumberland Farms in Winthrop, about a mile, and only in the AM, and im willing to pay $30 a week for the favor. Hope someone out there can help! Thanks!!
